'795 is as we said above a paraphrase of sensibili: Lucr. means that the smallest sensible time is about equal to the time in which we can utter one word, and that in that smallest time are latently contained many rational times, or times such as the mind can conceive by its reason to exist. Thus in the smallest thing perceptible to sight or touch are contained very many things which the reason alone can apprehend‚ viz. atoms or the parts of atoms.
